SELECT vendor_contracts.vendor_name, procurement_regulations.regulation_name FROM vendor_contracts INNER JOIN agreement_compliance ON vendor_contracts.contract_id = agreement_compliance.contract_id INNER JOIN procurement_regulations ON agreement_compliance.regulation_id = procurement_regulations.regulation_id;

SELECT r.regulation_name, a.compliance_status FROM procurement_regulations r JOIN agreement_compliance a ON r.regulation_id = a.regulation_id WHERE a.compliance_status = true;
SELECT v.vendor_name, SUM(a.compliance_status::int) AS total_compliance_count FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name;

SELECT v.vendor_name, COUNT(a.compliance_status) AS total_agreements FROM vendor_contracts v LEFT JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name HAVING COUNT(a.compliance_status) > 0;

SELECT v.vendor_name, AVG(c.contract_amount) AS avg_contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v WHERE v.vendor_name LIKE '%Inc%' JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id WHERE a.compliance_status = true GROUP BY v.vendor_name;
SELECT r.regulation_name, COUNT(a.compliance_id) AS total_compliance FROM procurement_regulations r JOIN agreement_compliance a ON r.regulation_id = a.regulation_id GROUP BY r.regulation_name;

SELECT v.vendor_name, MAX(c.contract_amount) AS max_contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name;

SELECT v.vendor_name, MIN(c.contract_amount) AS min_contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name;

SELECT v.vendor_name, AVG(c.contract_amount) AS avg_contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name HAVING AVG(c.contract_amount) > 5000;
SELECT v.vendor_name, COUNT(DISTINCT a.regulation_id) AS unique_regulations FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name;

SELECT v1.vendor_name AS vendor_1, v2.vendor_name AS vendor_2, COUNT(DISTINCT a.regulation_id) AS shared_regulations FROM vendor_contracts v1 JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v1.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts v2 ON a.contract_id = v2.contract_id WHERE v1.vendor_name < v2.vendor_name GROUP BY v1.vendor_name, v2.vendor_name;

SELECT r.regulation_name, COUNT(c.contract_id) AS total_contracts FROM procurement_regulations r JOIN agreement_compliance a ON r.regulation_id = a.regulation_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id GROUP BY r.regulation_name;
SELECT v.vendor_name, AVG(a.compliance_status::int) AS compliance_rate FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id GROUP BY v.vendor_name;

SELECT v.vendor_name, a.compliance_status, c.contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id WHERE c.contract_amount > 1000;

SELECT v.vendor_name, AVG(c.contract_amount) AS avg_contract_amount FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id JOIN vendor_contracts c ON a.contract_id = c.contract_id WHERE a.compliance_status = true GROUP BY v.vendor_name HAVING AVG(c.contract_amount) > 5000;

SELECT r.regulation_name, COUNT(*) AS total_compliance FROM procurement_regulations r JOIN agreement_compliance a ON r.regulation_id = a.regulation_id WHERE a.compliance_status = true GROUP BY r.regulation_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 1;

SELECT v.vendor_name, COUNT(*) AS total_compliance FROM vendor_contracts v JOIN agreement_compliance a ON v.contract_id = a.contract_id WHERE a.compliance_status = true GROUP BY v.vendor_name HAVING COUNT(*) > 2;
